EDA for flights data

Alexander Kolupaev

11/04/2017

About

The data set contains information flight delays and performance for domestic carriers in the United States. The year of 2016 is considered in the analysis. The data set can be accessed from RITA.

I will only focus on the 4 biggest airlines with combined market share of about 70%. Those are:

  • Southwest
  • Delta
  • American
  • United

Reshaping

I am only interested in 4 airlines. Moreover, I only want to look at delays due to the carrier. Therefore I only leave variables and airlines of interest. Variables include:

  • total flights (arr_flights)
  • flights delayed (arr_del15)
  • total minutes delayed (arr_delay)
  • total minutes delayed because of carrier (carrier_delay)

Summarise

I group by month and carrier and calculate two ratios:

  • ratio of flights delayed
  • share of delay because of carrier

Plotting

we see that July sucks for delays, but its not carriers’ fault delta airlines even works harder to prevent delays: hence the lower spike in delayed flights for them.
